Recent advances in metabolomics, metatranscriptomics, and metagenomics has helped to bridge the knowledge gap, shedding light on the activity of individual biocontrol agents within soils, the rhizosphere, and the endosphere, including the metabolic potential of the entire microbial community associated with plants (
Figure 2
).

